    {
      "id": "how-it-moves",
      "textHash": "5edb6d24ba5530a753f3f4c028f7e4988a2ec5f01086712dc5116e2677088d28",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-live-migration/how-it-moves.5edb6d24.mp3",
      "narrationText": "It works in two phases. Phase one copies the bulk while the app keeps running. Phase two checkpoints the live processes, carries over the final delta plus the process state, and resumes everything on the new machine. So the downtime is the delta, not the data. And the app never knows it moved.",
